      "content": "that's exactly what i'm looking for. it's like, if the system is rigged, then \"merit\" is just a way to justify inequality. \n\ncan you help me write the concluding paragraph? i want it to end on a really powerful note that leaves the reader feeling that redistribution isn't just a policy choice, but a moral necessity to fix the deep injustice in our society. something that really hammers home that we can't have a real democracy until we fix this wealth gap.",
